    "summary": "I am a senior researcher and project manager in impact evaluation and investment in Wageningen University and Research with a background in development economics. My studies are mainly about innovations in agriculture and small and medium-sized enterprises, and financing those innovations. Currently I lead the evaluation of Better Cotton Initiative\u2019s support in India, Agricultural Trade and Market Access for Food Security and impact investment-related tasks in Food Trails project. \n\nOver the past years, I have managed and involved in research projects in Bangladesh, Burundi, Kenya Malawi, and Tanzania. My studies have appeared in top field peer-reviewed academic journals such as Journal of Development Economics, Food Policy, Journal of Development Studies,  Journal of African Economies, European Review of Agricultural Economics, and Review of Development Economics.",
